Winona Ryder has appeared in photos wearing a men’s three-piece suit as she attended the Stranger Things Season four part one premiere. The event was held this Saturday in Brooklyn. The star matched the suit with a classic white dress shirt and without a tie. She completed her look with a black handbag and matching shoes. Winona also accessorised the look with a pin which contained a drawing of her Stranger Things character Joyce Byers. The actress attended the star-studded event alongside her boyfriend Scott Mackinlay Hahn. Scott came dressed in a creased black suit and matching dress shirt, with the top button undone. Winona posed alongside the rest of the Stranger Things cast on the red-carpet. The star’s character Joyce Byers is mother to Will Byers, one of the protagonists and the child who went missing in the first season of the show.